<div id="careers">

	<div class="sectionTextCenterJob">
		<p>
			<span class="sectionTextHeadlineCareer">SQL Server Development DBA</span>
	</div>

	<div class="sectionTextJob">
		<p>
			AltSource, Inc. is a successful and rapidly growing custom software development company located in SE Portland.
			We've been building enterprise systems since 2004 and are always on the lookout for smart and qualified people
			to join our team and help drive application design and implementation using Microsoft-centric technologies.
			We have deep domain knowledge in our application space, and our solutions make a daily positive impact on people's lives.
		</p>

		<p>
			We currently have an opening for a mid-to-senior level DBA to join the in-house database team.
		</p>

		<p>
			This position is development-focused with the primary role being to work directly with application development teams
			during application feature development, release and support. In addition, this position will work directly with the data
			architecture team to ensure ongoing development activities align with long-term enterprise goals.
		</p>

		<p>
			This position is best suited for someone able to embrace an agile-focused approach to development and an eagerness to
			interact and collaborate directly with development teams on a daily basis while providing hands on database support and
			guidance to developers and operations.
		</p>

		<p>
			This position includes assisting the operations team and production DBAs where needed of in-house and client database
			servers as well as keeping systems tuned and performing at optimal performance levels. Platforms include Microsoft SQL
			Server 2008, 2012, 2014, .NET, Windows Servers (2008/2012), Virtual environments (VMWare/Hyper-V) and bare metal servers.
		</p>

		<p><span class="careerHeadline">Responsibilities:</span><br>
		</p>
		<ul id="jobList">
			<li>Assist development teams in the build out of schema and database technologies</li>
			<li>Ensure use of best practices for data-driven applications within development teams</li>
			<li>Review and optimize application data access strategies</li>
			<li>Enforce database quality standards within the code base</li>
			<li>Support and build out development and QA database environments</li>
			<li>Build out and maintain reporting services and integration services applications</li>
			<li>Mentor developers and product owners on database patterns</li>
			<li>Prepare scripts for deployment and automation</li>
			<li>Create, implement and maintain policies and procedures regarding data security/access, retention/destruction, and backup recovery functions</li>
			<li>Monitor hardware, software, storage and performance of database servers</li>
			<li>Tune and configure database servers for best sustainable performance</li>
			<li>Support architecture team in long-term planning and implementation</li>
			<li>Support after-hours and on-call duties as required</li>
			<li>Support operations and support teams and assist with troubleshooting activities as needed</li>
			<li>Continue to develop your skills in database optimization, data integrity, and other DBA duties as a member of an agile software team</li>
		</ul>

	
		<p><span class="careerHeadline">We want to work with you if:</span><br>
		</p>
		<ul id="jobList">
			<li>You can visualize the big picture and analyze key issues and recommend effective solutions.</li>
			<li>You can create and maintain processes in line with requirements for project goals.</li>
			<li>You have strong opinions on how things should be built, yet are flexible in achieving solutions.</li>
			<li>You work well in an agile team environment where process and schedules can change quickly.</li>
			<li>You want to make an impact and not just be a cog in the machine.</li>
			<li>You are a smart, creative, proactive problem solver.</li>
		</ul>

	
		<p><span class="careerHeadline">Requirements:</span><br>
		</p>
		<ul id="jobList">
			<li>B.S. in Computer Science, Management Information Systems or related field</li>
			<li>5+ years experience as a SQL Server DBA</li>
			<li>Experience working with platforms listed above</li>
			<li>Strong knowledge of T-SQL programming language</li>
			<li>Solid understanding of transactional (OLTP) workload fundamentals</li>
			<li>Extensive knowledge of SQL Server internals and best practices for highly concurrent systems</li>
			<li>High level of proficiency in database design fundamentals for e-commerce, CRM and Inventory management systems a plus</li>
			<li>Working knowledge and experience developing and deploying SSRS reports</li>
			<li>Experienced with source control applications (SVN, TFS, GIT, etc.)</li>
			<li>Knowledge of C# and .Net web technologies a big plus</li>
			<li>Experience with Visual Studio 2013+</li>
			<li>Exposure to Azure cloud technologies a plus</li>
			<li>Experience working with PowerShell a plus</li>
			<li>Experience with large and very large RDBMS a plus</li>
			<li>A great team attitude and the desire to work with a small group of your peers, without hierarchy or politics.</li> 
		</ul>

	</div>
</div>
<div id="careerFooterText">
		<p>To apply, please e-mail your cover letter and resume to <a href="mailto:join@altsrc.net">join@altsrc.net</a>. 
		To learn more about us, please visit our web site at <a href="../index.html" rel="nofollow">www.altsrc.net</a> or Facebook page at 
		<a href="https://www.facebook.com/AltSource" rel="nofollow">www.facebook.com/AltSource</a>.
		</p>	
